00:59:03,611 --> 00:59:04,912
HE'S A FRIEND.

942
00:59:04,945 --> 00:59:07,948
MY NAME IS ELROI, SIR.

943
00:59:09,817 --> 00:59:17,691
I'M GONNA HELP YOU GET YOUR DAUGHTER OFF THIS PLACE.

944
00:59:17,725 --> 00:59:21,862
TELL ME, MRS. CARBERRY, WHAT LED YOU TO BELIEVE I MIGHT

945
00:59:21,896 --> 00:59:24,798
BE INTERESTED IN SELLING OFF A PIECE OF MY LAND?

946
00:59:24,832 --> 00:59:27,034
AN EDUCATED GUESS, MR. CLAY.

947
00:59:27,067 --> 00:59:30,871
ACCORDING TO YOUR NEIGHBORS, THAT PARCEL HAS LAIN FALLOW

948
00:59:30,905 --> 00:59:31,972
FOR SEVERAL YEARS.

949
00:59:32,006 --> 00:59:34,975
AND WITH TOBACCO PRICES DOWN THE WAY THEY ARE,

950
00:59:35,009 --> 00:59:37,978
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT BE OPEN TO A FAIR OFFER.

951
00:59:38,012 --> 00:59:40,681
NOW, OF COURSE, IF I'M MISTAKEN, THERE MIGHT BE OTHER

952
00:59:40,714 --> 00:59:42,383
PLANTERS I COULD TALK TO.

953
00:59:42,416 --> 00:59:44,451
THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.

954
00:59:44,485 --> 00:59:45,653
YOUR OFFER IS GENEROUS.

955
00:59:45,686 --> 00:59:47,655
I'M SURE WE CAN COME TO AN AGREEMENT.

956
00:59:47,688 --> 00:59:50,224
BUT I AM CURIOUS ABOUT ONE THING.

957
00:59:50,257 --> 00:59:54,194
30 ACRES IS NO SMALL UNDERTAKING.

958
00:59:54,228 --> 00:59:56,063
HOW WILL YOU MANAGE ON YOUR OWN?

959
00:59:56,096 --> 00:59:58,332
WE IRISH HAVE NEVER BEEN AFRAID OF HARD WORK, MR. CLAY.

960
00:59:58,365 --> 01:00:00,768
BESIDES, I LEARNED A GREAT DEAL ABOUT BUSINESS FROM

961
01:00:00,801 --> 01:00:02,536
MY LATE HUSBAND.

962
01:00:02,570 --> 01:00:05,406
A GOOD BUSINESS MIND WILL ONLY TAKE YOU SO FAR.

963
01:00:05,439 --> 01:00:08,008
YOU'LL NEED STRONG BACKS TO WORK THIS LAND.

964
01:00:08,042 --> 01:00:11,712
I'M SORRY, I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

965
01:00:11,745 --> 01:00:13,247
WELL, SLAVES, DEAR.

966
01:00:13,280 --> 01:00:17,518
SURELY YOU'LL WANT TO BUY YOURSELF SOME GOOD NIGRAS.

967
01:00:17,551 --> 01:00:18,919
AYE, OF COURSE, I'M SORRY.

968
01:00:18,953 --> 01:00:20,421
I'VE HAD A VERY LONG DAY.

969
01:00:20,454 --> 01:00:24,692
IN FACT, I'VE TAKEN UP FAR TOO MUCH OF YOUR TIME.

970
01:00:24,725 --> 01:00:27,061
I WONDER IF YOU'D BE KIND ENOUGH TO ASK MY DRIVER

971
01:00:27,094 --> 01:00:28,295
TO COME ROUND.

972
01:00:28,329 --> 01:00:31,098
OH, NONSENSE, MRS. CARBERRY, YOU'LL BE OUR GUEST TONIGHT.

973
01:00:31,131 --> 01:00:33,968
THEN WE CAN CONCLUDE OUR BUSINESS IN THE MORNING.

974
01:00:34,001 --> 01:00:36,370
WELL, I'M VERY GRATEFUL.

975
01:00:36,403 --> 01:00:38,739
WHERE SHALL I HAVE MY SLAVE SLEEP?

976
01:00:38,772 --> 01:00:40,507
I WOULDN'T FRET, DEAR.

977
01:00:40,541 --> 01:00:43,243
I'M SURE HE'S ALREADY FOUND HIMSELF A NICE SPOT FOR

978
01:00:43,277 --> 01:00:44,311
THE NIGHT.

979
01:00:44,345 --> 01:00:48,248
IF THERE'S ONE THING NIGRAS LOVE TO DO, IT'S SLEEP.

980
01:00:48,282 --> 01:00:51,018
NOW, IT TAKE A MAN TEN MINUTES TO MAKE IT TO

981
01:00:51,051 --> 01:00:53,988
THE CREEK, FOLLOW IT DOWNSTREAM TO WHERE IT GETS

982
01:00:54,021 --> 01:00:56,390
SHALLOW, AND THEN FROM THERE, IT'S JUST A STRETCH OF FIELD

983
01:00:56,423 --> 01:00:57,291
TO NEWCASTLE.

984
01:00:57,324 --> 01:00:58,525
THAT WOULD TAKE AN ETERNITY.

985
01:00:58,559 --> 01:01:00,728
I SAY WE USE THE SHADE OF THE TREES, AND FOLLOW

986
01:01:00,761 --> 01:01:01,929
THE ROAD ALL THE WAY TO TOWN.

987
01:01:01,962 --> 01:01:03,063
THAT WOULD BE HALF THE TIME.

988
01:01:03,097 --> 01:01:04,198
NOW, THAT'S FOOL-HEADED.

989
01:01:04,231 --> 01:01:07,001
THEM SLAVE-CATCHERS' HOUNDS WILL BE ON YOUR TAIL BEFORE

990
01:01:07,034 --> 01:01:08,769
YOU'RE A MILE OFF THE PLANTATION.

991
01:01:08,802 --> 01:01:10,904
THAT CREEK'S THE ONLY WAY TO THROW THEM DOGS.

992
01:01:10,938 --> 01:01:14,708
YOU TAKE YOUR WAY, YOU'RE GONNA GET MARY KILLED.

993
01:01:14,742 --> 01:01:16,110
LOOK, THIS IS MY PLAN.

994
01:01:16,143 --> 01:01:28,088
YOU NEED TO MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS AND STAY OUT OF MINE.

995
01:01:28,122 --> 01:01:30,991
HOW COULD YOU SAY THAT TO HIM?

996
01:01:31,025 --> 01:01:32,393
MARY.

997
01:01:37,131 --> 01:01:38,365
[ SIGH ]  MRS. CARBERRY.

998
01:01:45,239 --> 01:01:46,840
YES?

999
01:01:46,874 --> 01:01:50,411
MRS. CARBERRY, IF I MAY ASK A PERSONAL QUESTION.

1000
01:01:50,444 --> 01:01:56,283
YOUR HUSBAND, WAS HIS ILLNESS A LENGTHY ONE?

1001
01:01:56,316 --> 01:02:00,020
NO, HE DIED RATHER SUDDENLY, ACTUALLY.

1002
01:02:00,054 --> 01:02:04,992
OH, I'M SORRY.

1003
01:02:05,025 --> 01:02:07,528
BUT PERHAPS IT WAS GOD'S WAY TO SPARE YOU THE PAIN OF

1004
01:02:07,561 --> 01:02:09,697
LOSING HIM GRADUALLY.

1005
01:02:09,730 --> 01:02:12,533
YES, PERHAPS.

1006
01:02:14,501 --> 01:02:17,004
YOU'RE VERY BRAVE TO BE STARTING A NEW LIFE

1007
01:02:17,037 --> 01:02:18,005
FOR YOURSELF.

1008
01:02:18,038 --> 01:02:19,073
WELL, THANK YOU.

1009
01:02:20,808 --> 01:02:22,910
WELL, GOOD NIGHT.

1010
01:02:22,943 --> 01:02:24,912
GOOD NIGHT.

1011
01:02:32,019 --> 01:02:34,421
[ WOMAN SINGING SPIRITUAL ]  MARY?

1012
01:03:06,720 --> 01:03:15,763
I KNOW YOU HAVE EVERY REASON TO HATE ME.

1013
01:03:15,796 --> 01:03:21,769
I ONLY WANTED THE BEST FOR YOU.

1014
01:03:21,802 --> 01:03:23,904
[ SOBBING ]  I'M SORRY.

1015
01:03:39,653 --> 01:03:42,856
THANK YOU FOR YOUR HOSPITALITY, MR. CLAY.

1016
01:03:42,890 --> 01:03:45,125
I'LL WIRE MY BANK AS SOON AS I GET BACK TO THE HOTEL.

1017
01:03:45,159 --> 01:03:47,194
I SHOULD HAVE MONEY FOR YOU BY WEEK'S END.

1018
01:03:47,227 --> 01:03:49,096
I LOOK FORWARD TO YOUR NEXT VISIT.

1019
01:03:49,129 --> 01:03:50,164
THANK YOU, SIR.

1020
01:03:50,197 --> 01:03:51,865
JAMES?

1021
01:04:07,848 --> 01:04:09,750
[ CHURCH BELL TOLLS ] I HAVE THE DRAFT.

1022
01:04:15,322 --> 01:04:18,826
THAT'S A LOT TO PAY FOR LAND WE WILL NEVER USE.

1023
01:04:18,859 --> 01:04:20,394
OH, JAMES, LOOK.

1024
01:04:22,696 --> 01:04:24,765
IT'S KITCHEL, JOHNSON'S MAN.

1025
01:04:24,798 --> 01:04:26,266
STAY HERE.

1026
01:04:26,300 --> 01:04:27,301
NO.

1027
01:04:27,334 --> 01:04:28,268
I SAID, STAY HERE.

1028
01:04:28,302 --> 01:04:29,837
STOP, PLEASE.

1029
01:04:34,408 --> 01:04:39,513
[ DOOR CLOSES ]  JOHNSON, THAT YOU?

1030
01:04:39,546 --> 01:04:41,782
JOHNSON?

1031
01:04:54,061 --> 01:04:55,195
JOHNSON?

1032
01:05:06,707 --> 01:05:08,242
KITCHEL.

1033
01:05:08,275 --> 01:05:09,943
[ BANG ] WHERE'S WILLIAM JOHNSON?

1034
01:05:21,288 --> 01:05:23,423
I AIN'T TELLING YOU NOTHING.

1035
01:05:26,293 --> 01:05:28,161
WHERE IS HE?

1036
01:05:28,195 --> 01:05:29,129
JAMES!

1037
01:05:29,162 --> 01:05:30,063
GET OUT OF HERE, ELIZABETH.

1038
01:05:30,097 --> 01:05:32,299
REMEMBER WHY WE'VE COME.

1039
01:05:36,503 --> 01:05:38,305
GET ME SOME ROPE.

1040
01:05:39,640 --> 01:05:41,241
REVEREND BRENNEMAN?

1041
01:05:43,277 --> 01:05:44,511
WE MUST GO NOW.

1042
01:05:44,544 --> 01:05:45,679
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

1043
01:05:45,712 --> 01:05:48,248
WILLIAM JOHNSON, THAT BASTARD WHO STOLE MARY,

1044
01:05:48,282 --> 01:05:49,483
HE'S IN TOWN.

1045
01:05:49,516 --> 01:05:50,918
I HAD A RUN-IN WITH HIS MAN.

1046
01:05:50,951 --> 01:05:53,353
I MADE SURE HE CAN'T FOLLOW US, BUT IT WON'T BE LONG

1047
01:05:53,387 --> 01:05:54,588
BEFORE JOHNSON FINDS US.

1048
01:05:54,621 --> 01:05:55,589
BUT WE NEED MORE TIME.

1049
01:05:55,622 --> 01:05:56,823
WE DON'T HAVE TIME.

1050
01:05:56,857 --> 01:05:57,991
WE MUST GO NOW.

1051
01:05:58,025 --> 01:05:59,526
WE MAY NOT HAVE ANOTHER CHANCE.

1052
01:05:59,559 --> 01:06:01,161
THEN WE'LL HAVE TO MAKE DO.

1053
01:06:01,194 --> 01:06:11,238
AND MAY GOD ALMIGHTY PROTECT US.

1054
01:06:11,238 --> 01:06:21,982
AND MAY GOD ALMIGHTY PROTECT US.

1055
01:06:22,015 --> 01:06:24,117
I'LL WAIT FOR YOUR SIGN.

1056
01:06:24,151 --> 01:06:25,252
MRS. CARBERRY.

1057
01:06:25,285 --> 01:06:27,120
MR. CLAY, I'M SORRY TO INTRUDE.

1058
01:06:27,154 --> 01:06:29,756
SOMETHING URGENT HAS COME UP, AND I HAD TO SEE YOU AT ONCE.

1059
01:06:29,790 --> 01:06:31,291
PLEASE, COME IN.

1060
01:06:32,759 --> 01:06:34,227
HYAH.

1061
01:06:36,229 --> 01:06:37,264
MARY.

1062
01:06:37,297 --> 01:06:38,999
DADDY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

1063
01:06:39,032 --> 01:06:39,900
SOMETHING HAPPENED.

1064
01:06:39,933 --> 01:06:40,901
JOHNSON IS ON HIS WAY.

1065
01:06:40,934 --> 01:06:41,768
JOHNSON?

1066
01:06:41,802 --> 01:06:42,836
WE HAVE GOT TO GO.

1067
01:06:42,869 --> 01:06:44,871
BUT DADDY, I HAVEN'T EVEN SAID GOODBYE TO INDIGO,

1068
01:06:44,905 --> 01:06:45,872
TO ELROI.

1069
01:06:45,906 --> 01:06:47,374
I WISH WE HAD TIME.

1070
01:06:47,407 --> 01:06:48,675
BUT WE'VE GOT--  YOU GOING, AIN'T YOU?

1071
01:06:54,514 --> 01:06:56,450
THEN I'M GOING WITH YOU.

1072
01:06:56,483 --> 01:06:58,919
ELROI, IF THEY CATCH YOU, THEY'LL HANG YOU.

1073
01:06:58,952 --> 01:07:00,520
I GOT TO TAKE THAT CHANCE.

1074
01:07:00,554 --> 01:07:03,490
YOU CAN'T STAY HERE, AND I CAN'T STAY HERE WITHOUT YOU.

1075
01:07:03,523 --> 01:07:05,092
ELROI, IT'LL BE MUCH TOO DANGEROUS.

1076
01:07:05,125 --> 01:07:06,293
I DIDN'T MAKE PLANS FOR YOU.

1077
01:07:06,326 --> 01:07:07,561
I CAN HELP YOU, SIR.

1078
01:07:07,594 --> 01:07:09,563
I KNOW HOW THEM SLAVE-CATCHERS DO THINGS.

1079
01:07:09,596 --> 01:07:10,931
IT'S TOO RISKY.

1080
01:07:10,964 --> 01:07:20,207
DADDY, I'M NOT LEAVING WITHOUT HIM.

1081
01:07:20,240 --> 01:07:23,577
I'M SORRY FOR YOUR TROUBLES, MRS. CARBERRY.

1082
01:07:23,610 --> 01:07:26,179
I HOPE THE QUESTIONS CONCERNING YOUR HUSBAND'S

1083
01:07:26,213 --> 01:07:28,348
ESTATE CAN BE CLEARED UP QUICKLY.

1084
01:07:28,382 --> 01:07:29,916
YES, I HOPE SO, TOO.

1085
01:07:29,950 --> 01:07:32,786
UNFORTUNATELY, IT'S A MATTER I MUST SEE TO IN PERSON.

1086
01:07:32,819 --> 01:07:33,920
THANK YOU.

1087
01:07:33,954 --> 01:07:36,623
BUT I WANTED TO BE SURE THAT OUR BUSINESS WAS CONCLUDED

1088
01:07:36,656 --> 01:07:38,692
BEFORE I LEFT FOR THE CAROLINAS.

1089
01:07:38,725 --> 01:07:40,827
I THINK YOU'LL FIND THAT IN ORDER, SIR.

1090
01:07:40,861 --> 01:07:42,262
I'M VERY GRATEFUL.

1091
01:07:42,295 --> 01:07:44,765
BUT SURELY THIS COULD HAVE WAITED FOR YOUR RETURN.

1092
01:07:44,798 --> 01:07:48,702
BELIEVE ME, MR. CLAY, NOTHING IS MORE IMPORTANT TO ME

1093
01:07:48,735 --> 01:07:50,404
THAN FINISHING THIS UP.

1094
01:07:51,505 --> 01:07:53,306
ELROI.

1095
01:07:55,876 --> 01:07:57,511
BROUGHT YOU

1096
01:07:57,544 --> 01:07:59,713
SOME MORE FIREWOOD, MAMA.

1097
01:07:59,746 --> 01:08:07,854
IT'S GONNA LAST ME A LONG TIME, SON.

1098
01:08:07,888 --> 01:08:10,924
MAMA, I GOT SOMETHING TO TELL YOU.

1099
01:08:10,957 --> 01:08:21,001
LOOK HERE, ELROI, I MADE YOUR FAVORITE, SWEET JAMS.

1100
01:08:21,001 --> 01:08:27,674
LOOK HERE, ELROI, I MADE YOUR FAVORITE, SWEET JAMS.

1101
01:08:27,707 --> 01:08:30,677
I LOVE YOU, BOY.

1102
01:08:32,913 --> 01:08:34,881
I LOVE YOU, TOO, MAMA.

1103
01:08:39,619 --> 01:08:43,390
GO, GO.

1104
01:09:07,981 --> 01:09:20,894
WHAT THE-- [ DOOR OPENS ]

1105
01:09:20,927 --> 01:09:23,463
WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT THESE, BOY?

1106
01:09:23,497 --> 01:09:24,865
NOTHING, SIR.

1107
01:09:24,898 --> 01:09:32,939
YOU'D BEST NOT BE LYING TO ME.

1108
01:09:32,973 --> 01:09:34,741
WHAT WE GOING TO DO NOW?

1109
01:09:34,774 --> 01:09:40,514
WHEN HE COME TO, HE GONNA KNOW YOU'RE A PART OF THIS.

1110
01:09:40,547 --> 01:09:53,460
THEN WE'RE JUST GONNA HAVE TO CONVINCE HIM OTHERWISE.

1111
01:09:53,493 --> 01:09:54,961
OH.

1112
01:10:13,180 --> 01:10:14,347
COME ON.

1113
01:10:42,008 --> 01:10:43,977
WHOA, GIRL.

1114
01:10:44,010 --> 01:10:45,478
[ HORSE WHINNIES ] DAMN.

1115
01:10:53,386 --> 01:10:54,754
THIS WAY!

1116
01:10:57,557 --> 01:11:00,560
HURRY, HURRY!

1117
01:11:03,296 --> 01:11:05,098
IN THE WAGON.

1118
01:11:24,952 --> 01:11:26,854
EVERYTHING SEEMS TO BE IN ORDER.

1119
01:11:26,887 --> 01:11:29,423
WELL, IF YOU'LL JUST COUNTERSIGN, THEN WE'LL BE

1120
01:11:29,457 --> 01:11:31,125
NEIGHBORS, MR. CLAY.

1121
01:11:31,158 --> 01:11:33,327
INDEED.

1122
01:11:39,361 --> 01:11:41,663
[ ALARM BELL RINGS ]  GET THE HORSES.

1123
01:11:43,170 --> 01:11:44,272
WHAT IS IT, STROOPE?

1124
01:11:44,305 --> 01:11:45,239
ESCAPE, SIR.

1125
01:11:45,273 --> 01:11:47,275
IT'S ELROI AND THAT MULATTO GIRL.

1126
01:11:47,308 --> 01:11:49,977
THEY KNOCKED ME AND THE MA'AM'S NIGGER COLD.

1127
01:11:50,011 --> 01:11:50,945
OH, NO.

1128
01:11:50,978 --> 01:11:52,747
AND ALL THE HORSES ARE ACCOUNTED FOR.

1129
01:11:52,780 --> 01:11:54,081
I'M GUESSING THEY'RE ON FOOT.

1130
01:11:54,115 --> 01:11:56,417
MRS. CARBERRY, PLEASE FORGIVE THIS INTERRUPTION.

1131
01:11:56,450 --> 01:11:58,319
OBVIOUSLY, I'M GOING TO BE INDISPOSED FOR THE NEXT

1132
01:11:58,352 --> 01:11:59,987
WHO-KNOWS-HOW-LONG.

1133
01:12:00,021 --> 01:12:02,490
PERHAPS WE CAN CONTINUE THIS BUSINESS LATER.

1134
01:12:02,523 --> 01:12:04,358
YES, OF COURSE.

1135
01:12:04,392 --> 01:12:05,426
GOOD DAY, THEN.

1136
01:12:05,459 --> 01:12:08,029
STROOPE, GATHER THE DOGS.

1137
01:12:12,600 --> 01:12:16,337
[ DOGS BARK ]  NO, MR. STROOPE,

1138
01:12:16,370 --> 01:12:17,605
PLEASE DON'T HURT ELROI.

1139
01:12:17,638 --> 01:12:18,839
GET OF MY WAY, INDIGO.

1140
01:12:18,873 --> 01:12:20,274
DON'T HURT MY BOY.

1141
01:12:20,308 --> 01:12:22,343
[ DOGS GROWL ]  PLEASE, MASTER,

1142
01:12:29,717 --> 01:12:31,852
HE A GOOD BOY.

1143
01:12:31,886 --> 01:12:33,688
PLEASE, YOU LOVE OLD INDIGO.

1144
01:12:35,289 --> 01:12:36,490
DO IT FOR ME.

1145
01:12:36,524 --> 01:12:37,825
I CAN'T DO THAT, INDIGO.

1146
01:12:37,858 --> 01:12:38,859
LET HIM GO!

1147
01:12:38,893 --> 01:12:40,361
MR. STROOPE.

1148
01:12:40,394 --> 01:12:42,163
PLEASE, PLEASE!

1149
01:12:42,196 --> 01:12:45,132
MASTER, DO IT FOR ME!

1150
01:12:45,166 --> 01:12:47,668
PLEASE, LET HIM GO.

1151
01:13:03,651 --> 01:13:15,029
THEY CAN'T BE STUPID ENOUGH TO HIDE IN THE HOUSE.

1152
01:13:15,062 --> 01:13:17,098
[ SHOUTS ]  WHAT THE HELL?

1153
01:13:25,139 --> 01:13:26,607
DO SOMETHING.

1154
01:13:26,640 --> 01:13:28,075
PERFUME.

1155
01:13:28,109 --> 01:13:31,212
WE'RE GONNA SEARCH EVERY ROAD AND FARM FROM HERE TO

1156
01:13:31,245 --> 01:13:33,681
NEWCASTLE UNTIL WE FIND THEM.

1157
01:13:33,714 --> 01:13:35,716
YES, SIR.

1158
01:13:35,750 --> 01:13:37,351
[ DOGS BARK AND GROWL ] [ HORSES WHINNY ]

1159
01:14:00,474 --> 01:14:01,475
MAMA!

1160
01:14:01,509 --> 01:14:03,778
OH, MAMA!

1161
01:14:03,811 --> 01:14:05,746
[ SOBBING ]  KITCHEL?

1162
01:14:20,494 --> 01:14:23,431
KITCHEL, WHERE THE HELL ARE YOU?

1163
01:14:23,464 --> 01:14:25,900
[ MUFFLED YELLING ]  WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

1164
01:14:30,171 --> 01:14:31,138
IT'S MINK.

1165
01:14:31,172 --> 01:14:32,940
HE CAME AFTER HIS DAUGHTER.

1166
01:14:37,144 --> 01:14:38,779
WE LEAVE AT FIRST LIGHT.

1167
01:14:38,813 --> 01:14:41,549
IT'S A TWO-DAY TRIP BY ROAD TO POINT PLEASANT ON THE

1168
01:14:41,582 --> 01:14:42,917
OHIO RIVER.

1169
01:14:42,950 --> 01:14:45,619
ONCE YOU'RE THERE, YOU'LL BE MET AND TAKEN ACROSS TO

1170
01:14:45,653 --> 01:14:48,456
THE OHIO SIDE AND SAFETY.

1171
01:14:48,489 --> 01:14:51,459
BUT THERE'S STILL 200 MILES FROM PORT PLEASANT TO CANADA.

1172
01:14:51,492 --> 01:14:53,861
200 OF THE SWEETEST MILES THIS SIDE OF HEAVEN, SIR.

1173
01:14:53,894 --> 01:14:55,896
SLAVE FOLK CALL IT THE "FRONT PORCH OF

1174
01:14:55,930 --> 01:14:56,997
THE PROMISED LAND."

1175
01:14:57,031 --> 01:14:58,866
